# 4. 噂

Haruka: (What's going on...? Mr. Hiiragi pushed for this to happen...?)
TV Station Staff Member's Voice: But I understand completely why you decided to go with ReLight, Mr. Nakano!
TV Station Staff Member's Voice: On top of being the talk of the town, they've got the backing of a huge agency.
TV Station Staff Member's Voice: So, given the choice between MORE MORE JUMP! and ReLight... It's really a no-brainer, right?
Nakano's Voice: Right...
Nakano's Voice: I still do believe that MORE MORE JUMP! is a great group with a lot of growth potential...
Nakano's Voice: However, if we're thinking about long-term stability, then ReLight is the correct way to go.
TV Station Staff Member's Voice: Exactly. But still... When's the last time Mr. Hiiragi personally came over to pitch his group?
Haruka: ...!
Haruka: (He came himself...?)
Haruka: (That means...)
Haruka: (No, there's nothing strange about a producer coming over to pitch his or her own group...)
Haruka: (If anything, it's perfectly normal to do so since you want them to succeed.)
Haruka: (It doesn't matter if MORE MORE JUMP! is competing for the same spot. I know that.)
Haruka: (Still...)
Magazine Editor: O-Oh, look at the time! I have to get to a meeting!
Stagehand: Uhh... I need to help out over at my next set! Sorry, Haruka. See you later.
Haruka: ...
Haruka: (We hit a sudden dry spell after Idol Lovers...)
Haruka: (If someone else's actions are behind us not receiving offers during that period...)
Hiiragi: I can't say I have heard anything. I'm not sure I can help you.
TV Station Staff Member's Voice: It seems like Mr. Hiiragi has been investing a lot of his time into ReLight after Idol Lovers.
Nakano's Voice: They did start getting a ton of attention after that event. I'd also want to make the most of this opportunity.
TV Station Staff Member's Voice: I agree. In that sense, he really is a savvy producer.
Nakano's Voice: He's always been passionate about what he does.
Nakano's Voice: Between how that event went and Mr. Hiiragi's marketing skills, every show wants ReLight right now.
TV Station Staff Member's Voice: Haha. Very true! Still...
TV Station Staff Member's Voice: There's also that scary rumor about Mr. Hiiragi. I hope it's not true, but it's probably best not to rock the boat.
Haruka: (What rumor...?)
TV Station Staff Member's Voice: Wait, I have to start getting ready to go location scouting...
Nakano's Voice: I also need to get to the studio... I'll see you later!
TV Station Staff Member's Voice: Okay, see you!
Haruka: (What they just said...)
Haruka: (If...)
Haruka: (If Mr. Hiiragi is behind our offers just stopping all of the sudden...)
Hiiragi: Above all else, I would never lose sight of my goals.
Haruka: ...
???: Kiritani?
Haruka: Huh...?
